  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (1143e57 2023-08-24T00:20:21.116511461Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test -vvv\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n**Context**:\r\n- doing invariant tests\r\n- test contract with invariant checks\r\n- handler contract with multiple functions that do assertions\r\n- explicitly force one of the handler functions to fail an assert\r\n- `fail_on_revert` = true\r\n\r\n**Action**: run `forge test -vvv`\r\n**Expected**: execution breaking, but to see the execution trace for the failing assertion printed\r\n**Observed**: execution breaks, but no execution trace printed\r\n\r\nI know that the docs say `- 3: Print execution traces for failing tests` and technically this is a handler failing and not the test contract, but this does count as a revert by forge\r\n\r\nNote: `assert(false)` in the test function works as expected, printing the execution trace\r\n\r\n**Resources**: created a repo with the tests\r\nhttps://github.com/omnifient/fuzzing-around/blob/main/test/invariant/TestHandlerWithFailingFunction.invariants.t.sol\r\nhttps://github.com/omnifient/fuzzing-around/blob/main/test/invariant/HandlerWithFailingFunction.sol",
