    "body": "yeah, with -vvvv I'm able to see the traces, but it's going to print for all executions (successful and failing)\r\n\r\n@Evalir on another note, what's the expectation for the number of times handler functions run vs the test functions?\r\n\r\nin a previous forge version, execution was 1 handler function : 1 test function\r\n\r\nbut in the latest version, it's not\r\nhere's a print from that repo (`t1` and `t2` are test functions)\r\n\r\n```\r\nLogs:\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  --- handlerC 115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639932\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  +++ t1\r\n  --- handlerA (fails) 115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935\r\n  +++ t1\r\n\r\n[PASS] invariantTestHandlerWithFailingFunction2() (runs: 2, calls: 27, reverts: 1)\r\nLogs:\r\n  +++ t2\r\n  --- handlerA (fails) 992\r\n  +++ t2\r\n```\r\n\r\naccording to the prints, \r\n1. the test function is being called multiple times without any handler function called before\r\n2. then it calls a handler function\r\n3. then it calls a test function two times in a row\r\n\r\nis there no guarantee of execution between handler/test?",
